narratives.question_text: What were the strengths and weaknesses of your Teaching Fellow as an instructor and how might his/her teaching be improved?
comments: Instructor: Ryan Michael Darr  Ryan did a good job when he was leading the class discussion. The only thing he could work on is being sure that the discussions and questions are given in a way that involves everyone in the discussion rather than just the individual, or few, students going back and forth and/or asking questions. Overall great though. I loved how prepared he came.
Instructor: Ryan Michael Darr  Ryan was very considerate and had very helpful comments on my paper project.
Instructor: Ryan Michael Darr  Ryan was very knowledgeable and offered good feed back. I did not spend enough time with him to asses any weaknesses

Instructor: Ryan Michael Darr  Ryan, was so helpful when I had to present. He sat down with me and really ended his expertise in the material. He is very knowledgeable of the material and did not mind taking the time to ensure that the students understood it.

Instructor: Ryan Michael Darr  Ryan came well prepared to facilitate the discussion on Kierkegaard. He had a commanding understanding of the argument and helped me to understand exactly where Kierkegaard stands in regards to Scandinavian Social welfare policies and to dissipate my confusion on this subject.
Instructor: Ryan Michael Darr  Ryan was so available and generous, very encouraging.
Instructor: Ryan Michael Darr  Ryan was helpful in discussing both the presentations and the papers. He also did an excellent job in leading discussion.
Instructor: Ryan Michael Darr  Very knowledgable about the subject matter and easy to talk to about issues. Ryan was a great Teaching Fellow.
Instructor: Ryan Michael Darr  He was very approachable to discuss any topic
Instructor: Ryan Michael Darr  Ryan was very helpful, organized and encouraging.
